Scott Quinnell (born 20 August 1972 in Morriston, Swansea, Glamorgan) is a Welsh former rugby union and rugby league player. He was a number 8 for Wales, Llanelli RFC, the Llanelli Scarlets, Richmond and the British and Irish Lions in rugby union. He won 52 caps for Wales (seven as captain) and three for the Lions, and scored 11 international tries for Wales and one for the Lions.
In 1994 he moved to Wigan in rugby league, and played two seasons, winning a league championship and two caps for Wales.
